<span id="freeTextContainer16319766051707691080">It&apos;s another book affirming the strong impact of families over generations--this time a Pakistani family. Given current news of increasing tensions (again) between Pakistan &amp; India, it should have had heightened interest (especially as it deals with those historical tensions&apos; effects on this family), but the prose was too cutesy, it didn&apos;t very successfully challenge the class divisions it purported to, &amp; was mostly just plain boring.</span>
