<span id="freeTextContainer3148607233849651338">It was a bit difficult to follow (lack of chronology, many unfamiliar names, and a lot of this fictional family&apos;s history), but I did enjoy the overall plot and the revelations and epiphanies of the main character. Unfortunately, the end was weak and rushed -- though I wonder if that was intentional -- and I was left with a feeling of slight dissatisfaction. </span>
  <span id="freeText3148607233849651338" style="display:none">It was a bit difficult to follow (lack of chronology, many unfamiliar names, and a lot of this fictional family's history), but I did enjoy the overall plot and the revelations and epiphanies of the main character. Unfortunately, the end was weak and rushed -- though I wonder if that was intentional -- and I was left with a feeling of slight dissatisfaction. </span>
